'''2009年卫星碰撞'''是人类有史以来首次[[近地轨道|近地轨道]][[人造卫星|人造卫星]]碰撞事件。碰撞发生在[[格林尼治时间|格林尼治时间]]2月10日16:56<ref name="jsr">{{cite web |title=Orbital Stop Press |author=Jonathan McDowell |url=http://planet4589.org/space/jsr/latest.html |accessdate=2009-02-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090212165558/http://planet4589.org/space/jsr/latest.html |archivedate=2009-02-12 }}</ref><ref name="Space">{{cite news | url = http://www.space.com/news/090211-satellite-collision.html | publisher = Space.com | title = U.S. Satellite Destroyed in Space Collision | accessdate = 2009-02-13 | archive-date = 2009-02-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090213230913/http://www.space.com/news/090211-satellite-collision.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>，地点位于[[西伯利亚|西伯利亚]][[泰梅爾半島|泰梅爾半島]]上空约776公里处。<ref name="jsr"/><ref name="Space"/><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/02/11/AR2009021103387_pf.html | title = Debris From Satellites' Collision Said to Pose Small Risk to Space Station | author = Joel Achenbach | publisher = The Washington Post | date = February 12, 2009 | accessdate = 2011-10-09 | archive-date = 2019-03-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190308024459/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/02/11/AR2009021103387_pf.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>碰撞速度估计达到11.6公里／秒。

碰撞是发生在属于美国[[铱卫星|铱卫星公司]]的[[铱星|铱星]]33号和属于[[俄罗斯航天部队|俄罗斯航天部队]]的[[宇宙2251|宇宙2251]]卫星之间。碰撞发生时，铱星依然处于工作状态，而俄国卫星则已经被废弃多年。<ref name="Reuters">{{cite news | url = http://www.reuters.com/article/newsMaps/idUSTRE51A8IA20090211 | title = U.S., Russian satellites collide in space | publisher = Reuters | first = Jim | last = Wolf | date = February 11, 2009 | accessdate = 2009-02-13 | archive-date = 2009-02-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090215175257/http://www.reuters.com/article/newsMaps/idUSTRE51A8IA20090211 | dead-url = no }}</ref>一名俄罗斯发言人拒绝对碰撞发生时其卫星是否已经无法控制表态。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7885051.stm|title=Russian and US satellites collide|date=2009-02-12|publisher=BBC News|quote=Russia has not commented on claims the satellite was out of control|accessdate=2009-02-12|archive-date=2011-08-22|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/617V9XuwD?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7885051.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

[[美国国家航空航天局|美国国家航空航天局]]报告指出这次碰撞产生了大量由卫星残骸组成的[[太空垃圾|太空垃圾]]。目前，{{tsl|en|United States Space Surveillance Network|美国太空监视网}}（U.S. Space Surveillance Network）追踪到了超过500个碎片，而更多的碎片还有待发现。<ref name="Space"/>美国国家航空航天局还指出，这些碎片对国际空间站造成危害的可能性较小，虽然碰撞发生在空间站运行轨道上空约430公里。<ref name="AP">{{cite news | title = Big satellites collide 500 miles over Siberia | url = http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5grGfFhzFgjxK46MQHTwD1RgRUwCAD969P1500 | publisher = The Associated Press | first = Marcia | last = Dunn | date = February 12, 2009 | access-date = 2009-02-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090215142330/http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5grGfFhzFgjxK46MQHTwD1RgRUwCAD969P1500 | archive-date = 2009-02-15 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref name="Russian and US satellites collide">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7885051.stm|title=Russian and US satellites collide|date=2009-02-12|accessdate=2009-02-12|publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]|archive-date=2011-08-22|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/617V9XuwD?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7885051.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>但有中国科学家卻指碎片可能影响中国的[[太阳同步轨道|太阳同步轨道]]卫星。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-02/12/content_10809710.htm | title = China alert on U.S.-Russian satellite collision | publisher = [[新华网|Xinhua]] | year = 2009 | accessdate = 2009-02-13 | archive-date = 2009-02-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090213132717/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-02/12/content_10809710.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>

在此事件之前，曾经发生过多次小规模的碰撞事件，通常是事先计划好的实验或有意摧毁目标卫星的行为。<ref>[http://www.nasa.gov/pdf/167813main_RP-06-119_05-020-E_DART_Report_Final_Dec_27.pdf DART Mishap Investigation Board Final Report] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nasa.gov/pdf/167813main_RP-06-119_05-020-E_DART_Report_Final_Dec_27.pdf |date=20090219180802 }} January 4, 2007</ref>1996年，[[Cerise|Cerise]]卫星曾与太空垃圾发生过碰撞。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.gsfc.nasa.gov/scienceques2003/20040116.htm | title = Is it possible for two orbiting satellites to collide? | first = David | last = Stern | publisher = [[NASA|NASA]] | year = 2004 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090120034318/http://www.gsfc.nasa.gov/scienceques2003/20040116.htm | archivedate = 2009-01-20 | accessdate = 2009-02-13 }}</ref>

